  <p>Although the SHCP remains optimistic and expects Mexico's economy to grow 4.1% in 2022, there are several endogenous and exogenous factors that could influence the country's economic performance; such as the conflict between Russia and Ukraine, inflationary pressures, higher interest rates, etc. For this reason, international agencies such as Goldman Sachs and Moody's expect growth of only 1.4% and 1.1%, respectively.</p>

  <p>However, according to the Survey of Credit and Housing Needs for the first quarter of 2022, published by Infonavit, the Housing Purchase Intention Index was at the highest level observed since its launch in the first quarter of last year, which means that housing demand could register a better dynamic during the course of the year.</p>



